Description:
25 Acres

The sugar gum plantation will realize a financial return and I suggest anyone considering this property should look up sugar gum plantations on the internet.

Description:
Modern Family Property
Inspection is a must to appreciate all the qualities this property has to offer. Once inside you will realize the true expanse of this lovely home and the endless possibilities this property has to offer.
Extended and renovated in recent times making it a home for the larger family. Some of the features of the property include entertaining areas to suit everyone's needs, over-height ceilings, crisp lines, floating timber floors, theatre room with screen, undercover outdoor area and a fabulous new kitchen. The kitchen has been completely renovated with stone bench tops, self-closing drawers, walk-in pantry, quality appliances and a beautiful garden window.
The tastefully decorated master bedroom has a luxurious ensuite with its own bath and a massive WIR. The minor bedrooms all have BIRs and the children have their own play room with access to the study or family office. The home also has its own security system.
The massive rear yard is a blank canvas big enough for a game of footy. There is 15 x 6
metre shed with concrete flooring, dual roller door access and a glass slider perfect for the home business or indulgent man cave. Inspection of this property is a must.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
Stunning Victorian cottage on approx. 1 acre
This gorgeous property offers a high-end semi-rural lifestyle within a renovated 1850's Victorian cottage on approx. 1 acre. The quaint façade is enhanced by a beautifully formed cottage garden and 'chocolate box' white picket fence. The property boasts sweeping lawns, established and productive fruit trees and a rear paddock for animals or a prized pony. The semi-rural views are serene and private, and unique for an acre property within walking distance of town!
The interiors boast a wonderful 'old meets new' theme finished with professional flare. Lofty ceilings and hardwood floors underpin the charming and luxurious decor. Stained and frosted glass, decretive plasterwork and renovated sash windows hark back to a bygone era.
The light-filled floor plan begins with the traditional double fronted design providing 4 bedrooms with an elegant central hall. Bedrooms are romantic and bright, 1 with a gas log fire in the original fireplace, 1 with extensive robes and most with ceiling fans.
Further in, proper rejuvenation is achieved in the exquisite new bathroom featuring porcelain tiles, Caesarstone-topped vanity, a fully accessible walk-in shower, divine freestanding bath and back-to-wall toilet. A 2nd toilet, in the enormous laundry, is convenient.
The north facing living hub at the rear is breathtaking, capitalising on the beauty of the semi-rural surrounds with extension onto a deep undercover deck that wraps the north and east aspects. The tranquil indoor-outdoor lifestyle offered is second to none. The calibre of entertaining is enviable!
The kitchen is high-end with Caesarstone work surfaces, Ilve 900mm cooker, Siemens dishwasher and huge walk-in pantry. The dining area hugs floor-to-ceiling glazing, bright and inviting in the morning sun. Living is supremely comfortable with north facing picture windows flanking a built-in gas fireplace and flat screen TV. The modern Provincial decor is ideally matched to the location.
A 2nd living zone offers versatility, useful as a private lounge or home office. With deck access and garden views it's another outstanding room.
Climate can be tweaked in each room with the combination of a gas wall furnace, 2 split systems and a further air conditioner. Tailored year round comfort results!
Shedding provides precious space for stock feed or farm equipment, and adjoins a double carport for the family vehicles. Stylish exposed aggregate surfaces surround the home and deck.
13500L of tank water storage ensures well-watered gardens and produce. Along with the array of fruit trees, self-sufficiency can be achieved with the raised vegetable beds and chicken coop.
The privilege of space, convenience to town, luxurious interiors and opportunity to live with a level of self-sufficiency give this delightful home a leading edge. Don't hesitate! This one won't linger!
- Circa 1850 renovated cottage on approx.1 acre with fruit trees, shedding and a rear paddock
- Stunning 4-BR home with open plan living and lounge adjoining an expansive north deck
- High-end kitchen with Caesarstone, quality European appliances and large walk-in pantry
- Exquisite bathroom with walk-in shower, freestanding bath, toilet and 2nd toilet in laundry
- Gas fire places, split systems, double carport, 13500L of water storage, chicken coop
- Private and serene semi-rural views, and within walking distance of town
Land: 1 Acre approx.

Entering the market as one of the larger land parcels in the area, with potential to subdivide starting from 2 to 8 lots, ranging from 300 to 1,275 sqm allotments (STCA) and proposed drawing for 6 larger allotments to be provided by the vendor, this certainly is a lucrative investment. View without delay!

Description:
Grand Country Lifestyle
Nestled away is a quite court location, this property on 1 acre of approximate land is stunning. In an exclusive cul-de-sac the home offers the all residents a reserved, private, unique and flexible lifestyle. Within minutes to the township of Drysdale, some of peninsulas finest schooling facilities, along with being only 20 minutes from Geelong CDB and 5 minutes to all of the Bellarine Peninsulas makes this location convenient and practicable for the entire family.
Once past the circular drive way you are welcomed by a hidden oasis with a true country living feel, which then leads to a landscaped garden with lush green grass and retained garden beds. Upon entry to this residence you are welcomed by the first living, leading to the dining, overseeing the kitchen, meals and fourth family living zone. With rear yard views the kitchen, features dishwasher, glass hot plates with wall oven, stunning backlit display cupboards, a light filled walk in pantry finished with gloss white pot draws, breakfast bar with a bench top. The four living zones, are warmed by a gas log fire, split systems and ceiling fans.
On entry to the master bedroom a spacious walk in robe and en-suite with tactic shower, vanity and toilet are to the left. The three additional bedrooms are spacious, with built in robes and like the master they feature ceiling fans, block out blinds, down lights throughout and warmed by ducted gas heating. The family bathroom is central to all bedrooms and in a white colour palate feature, bath, shower, vanity, with additional separate toilet. The family laundry allows rear access via glass sliding doors offering an undercover verandah with views to the landscaped manicures gardens.
An outdoor undercover alfresco, is accessed via the fourth living by light filled glassed sliding doors which is an ideal paradise for the entertainers whilst overlooking the rear yard and fish ponds. The total of thirteen secure car parking options are made up of three colour bond garages with power. This includes one garage with four car parking options and another with six car spaces, a single colour bond garage, plus a remote controlled double lock up garage which is attached to the home with internal access. Additional features include a wood and tool shed, water tanks with an irrigated to water the established and extremely maintained landscaped gardens.
This brick home is a beautiful delight, complementing the relaxed, tranquil and serene country lifestyle we all truly desire consequently ideal for diverse family or professionals seeking a country change. With a relaxed vibe, make this property yours today. An inspection is a must.

Description:
TWO RESIDENCES, 15.5 ACRES ON THE BELLARINE
Step back in time with this 15.5 acre (approx) property with two residences. One built in the early 70's the other a more recent addition.
Your own private oasis complete with palm trees. Enter the driveway of the front property take a deep breath and take in the lush surrounding of the well-established gardens hiding the home from view of the road. Inside enjoy the well maintained dwelling that takes you back to the 70's. Many of us feel at home in this era. Classic layout enabling areas to be closed off for privacy and warmth. Nothing like a wood heater for the ambience and comfort in the middle of winter. Preparing meals in this kitchen will be so relaxing with the elevated view over the garden. Which is watered with tanks dotted around the property. Two living, three bedrooms all with BIR's, four car garage extra shedding and workshops.
In this wine and olive growing area on the Bellarine you will have the cellar to be able to keep your bounty in the dark should you choose to grow grapes or olives on this land. Currently there is a pine planation behind the second home and fenced paddocks for keeping the livestock safe. The current Vendors enjoy the sustainability of having sheep and spinning the wool having established for themselves a viable business adventure coupled with the horses that have enjoyed living in this environment too. Hobby farm with the potential of anything your imagination will allow.
The second residence up on the hill has magnificent views across to the You Yangs and the Bay. This farmhouse has no pretence which is just what you need to feel relaxed after a hard day on the land. Boots off and enjoy the wood heater and the views. Spacious kitchen that also looks out over the paddocks and animals grazing. Two living areas, good sized kitchen and four bedrooms plus study. Verandas surrounding the Cedar clad home, ample shedding.
A rural lifestyle but with a coastal option just down the road in Portarlington. Living here you would have no idea there was anyone else around. The trees and vegetation keep the noise away. You choose; you in one home family in another or you in one home and leasing the other. Options abound with this unusual property. Buy now and be settled in time to enjoy summer on the Bellarine.

Description:
A GRAND ORIGINAL VICTORIAN WITH SO MUCH SPACE INSIDE AND OUT (APPROX 2230 SQM)
A wealth of living and positioned in the village of Drysdale, close to the Rail Trail, schools, parklands and lake area, walk or ride to school from your home. Period features prevail with the lace and return verandah impressing immediately, spacious hallway, through to extra-large open plan living, meals and kitchen area, ornate doors open to two enticing garden spots, one undercover, shaded by a glorious white mulberry tree, the other to a delightful rambling slate paved area. Formal gracious lounge room with so much natural light the room changes with the day. The main bedroom has WIR and the ensuite/bathroom is 2 way, three more bedrooms, another central bathroom, powder room and laundry. A matured garden haven full of surprises with an abundance of fruit trees and so much more to delight. Features include cornices, leadlight, daddo, timber and pressed metal 11FT ceilings, fretwork, open fireplaces, slow combustion heater, bay windows, polished floors, fan, split system, tanks, quality window furnishings and Miele kitchen appliances. Front access has plenty of room for vehicles, rear access has double garage/workshop combined. This home will provide perfect living for the new owner...........a unique purchase. Opportunity for subdivision STCA, maybe Guest Accommodation.
